exports[`renderAgentsMd > matches snapshot 1`] = `
"# AGENTS.md

## Overview

- **Language:** TypeScript
- **Project type:** web-app
- **Framework:** Next.js 14 App Router
- **Primary dependencies:** next, react, tailwindcss, @radix-ui/react-slot, class-variance-authority, clsx, tailwind-merge

This file is for autonomous coding agents. Prefer the conventions and paths below over generic stack advice.

## Setup

Use the commands below when they are present; they are derived from project manifests in the repo snapshot.

## Commands

### Install

\`\`\`bash
pnpm install
\`\`\`

### Dev server

\`\`\`bash
pnpm dev
\`\`\`

### Build

\`\`\`bash
pnpm build
\`\`\`

### Test (full suite)

\`\`\`bash
pnpm test
\`\`\`

### Test (single path)

\`\`\`bash
pnpm test -- <path>
\`\`\`

### Lint

\`\`\`bash
pnpm lint
\`\`\`



## Conventions

### Naming

- **Files:** Kebab-case for \`app/\` route segments; PascalCase for components under \`components/\`. Colocate feature modules under \`features/<name>/\`.
- **Components:** PascalCase file names matching the default export. Prefer composing primitives from \`components/ui/\` (shadcn) rather than one-off styled divs.
- **Functions:** camelCase for utilities and hooks (\`useTheme\`). Event handlers prefixed with \`handle\` or passed as \`onX\` props.
- **Variables:** camelCase locals; SCREAMING_SNAKE only for true constants. Prefer \`const\` and narrow types with \`satisfies\` where helpful.

### Structure and behavior

Routes and layouts live in \`app/\` (App Router). Shared UI primitives live in \`components/ui/\` (shadcn). Shared helpers in \`lib/\` (e.g. \`lib/utils.ts\` with \`cn()\`). Global styles in \`app/globals.css\`; Tailwind v4 via \`@tailwindcss/postcss\`.

**Error handling:** Use \`try/catch\` in Server Actions and surface user-facing errors with Sonner toasts on the client. Prefer returning typed Result-like objects from server utilities when batching work.

**State:** React state and context for local UI; server state from \`fetch\` in Server Components. No global client store unless a route truly needs it.

### Shared building blocks

- **cn() helper** (\`lib/utils.ts\`): Merge Tailwind classes with \`tailwind-merge\` to avoid conflicting utilities.
- **Button variants** (\`components/ui/button.tsx\`): Use \`class-variance-authority\` (cva) for size and variant props on shadcn \`Button\`.
- **App layout shell** (\`app/layout.tsx\`): Root layout wraps providers (\`ThemeProvider\`, \`Toaster\`) and font loading.

**Things agents must not do:**

- Do not hand-edit \`components.json\` or generated shadcn files without running the CLI.
- Avoid fetching in Client Components when the same data can be loaded in a Server Component.
- Do not add new CSS files per page; extend Tailwind tokens or use \`cn()\` instead.

## Testing

- **Runner / stack:** Vitest

Vitest + Testing Library for components; colocate \`*.test.tsx\` next to components or under \`__tests__/\`. Run \`pnpm test\` from repo root.

Run the full test suite before proposing a merge; fix failures you introduce.

## Pull Request Guidelines

- Keep changes scoped; follow the file layout and naming rules above.
- Reuse abstractions listed under **Shared building blocks** instead of duplicating logic.
- Address every **Things agents must not do** item—do not introduce new violations.
- For the common workflow **Add a shadcn UI primitive**, follow:

1. Run \`pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component>\` from the repo root.
2. Import from \`@/components/ui/<component>\` in your feature code.
3. Use \`cn()\` from \`@/lib/utils\` when merging classes.
4. Run \`pnpm lint\` and \`pnpm test\` before opening a PR.
"
`;
